        "text_cDkcNe": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>MUD Jeans is the world's first circular denim brand. We create premium, stylish jeans that are ethically produced. Unlike other fashion brands, we take back old jeans and reuse the valuable raw materials to create new fabric and new jeans. With this closed-loop circular approach, we are an exemplary brand that demonstrates how to create a world without waste. Since 2015, we have been a B Corp and are recognized as the world's best B Corp for the environment. </p><p>At MUD Jeans, we are committed to a diverse, fair, and inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected. We believe that a diverse and motivated team is key to creating a financially healthy company that makes an impact.</p><p>We are looking for a:</p><p><strong>Sales Support Intern</strong></p><h2>Sales Support Intern <br/></h2><p>We are looking for an intern (meeloopstage) to join the sales support team. Our team makes sure that our customers, stores and agents worldwide are happy and that the order process of their MUD Jeans is easy and enjoyable. Are you enthusiastic about providing amazing sales support to an international network of customers and partners? Then we are looking for you!</p><h4><strong>Role & Responsibilities </strong><br/></h4><ul><li>Support the B2B sales support team in ensuring that all orders and systems run smoothly</li><li>Gain experience in managing backend data of products and an B2B online shop</li><li>Make our customers and wholesale partners happy by providing solutions and customer-oriented communication</li><li>Research and identify key market trends and client opportunities. </li><li>Take an active part in weekly team meetings to brainstorm ideas or improve processes and meet sales targets. </li></ul><h4><strong>What we ask for:</strong><br/></h4><ul><li>You are student at an MBO, HBO or WO or you are in a gap period and want to gain some practical experience</li><li>Start date immediately and you are available for 5-6 months or more </li><li>You are available for 40h/week and 3-4 days at the office in Laren</li><li>You have a structured way of working, attention for detail, and passion for sales</li><li>You are proficient in MS Office, especially Excel, experience with Shopify is a plus! </li><li>You are fluent in English, native Dutch and basic German is a plus!</li><li>You have good communication skills in writing and verbally</li><li>You are motivated to be part of a pioneer sustainable denim brand and a team player with an international team</li></ul><h4><strong>What you can expect:</strong><br/></h4><ul><li>Being part of an intrinsically motivated team in a B Corp that is pioneering in circular denim. You<br/>will be part of a small team that makes a difference in the world</li><li>A monthly compensation, and transport costs covered</li><li>24 vacation days (based on a year and a 40-hour workweek)</li><li>First free pair of MUD Jeans to welcome you to the team! Additional 73% discount on our whole collection and a 20% friends and family discount.</li><li>If you live in Amsterdam, there is an electric carpool option to the office</li></ul><h4><strong>Interested?</strong><br/></h4><p>If you are interested in this position, please respond with your CV and a short motivation in an email to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@mudjeans.eu\" target=\"_blank\">jobs@mudjeans.eu</a>.</p>",
